President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. These include Dino Falaschetti as the Director of the Office of Financial Research, Department of the Treasury; Michael A. Hammer as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Democratic Republic of the Congo; Rodney Hood as a Member of the National Credit Union Administration; and Kathleen Laura Kraninger as Director of the Bureau of Consumer Financial Protection. Additionally, Darla Romfo has been appointed as a Member of the Commission on Presidential Scholars.